There are a couple of issues with your code that may be causing it not to show any results on the search screen:

1. You're not passing the 'navigation' object to the 'handleSearch' function. You need to either pass it as a parameter or declare it before the function and use it inside the function. Try adding the following before the 'handleSearch' function:

const navigation = useNavigation();

2. You're not checking if the search term is empty before making the database query. This might be causing the query to return an empty result. Try adding the following check at the beginning of the 'handleSearch' function:

if(!searchTerm.trim()){
  setSearchResult([]);
  return;
}

This will set 'searchResult' to an empty array and return if the search term is empty or contains only whitespace.

3. You're not rendering the 'Result' component correctly on the search screen. Change the following line in the 'Search' component:

{results.length > 0 ? (
  results.map((item, index)=>
    <Result key={index} item={item}/>)
  ): (
  <Text>Не найдено.</Text>
)}

to:

