The issue seems to be with how you are retrieving the image data and passing it to the `firebase.storage()` method. Instead of using `setImageData` to set the state of your image data, you can use `response.uri` directly to upload the image to Firebase Storage.

Here is an updated `chooseImage` function that should work for you:

```
const chooseImage = async () => {
  try {
    const options = {
      mediaTypes: ImagePicker.MediaTypeOptions.Images,
      quality: 0.5,
    };
    const response = await ImagePicker.launchImageLibraryAsync(options);
    if (!response.cancelled) {
      const uri = response.uri;
      setImageData(uri);
    }
  } catch (error) {
