Sure! Here's an implementation of quicksort in Java using the Hoare partition scheme:

```
public class QuickSort {

    /**
     * Sorts an array of integers in ascending order using the Quick Sort algorithm
     * 
     * @param arr The array of integers to be sorted
     * @param low The starting index of the subarray to be sorted
     * @param high The ending index of the subarray to be sorted
     */
    public void quickSort(int[] arr, int low, int high) {
        if (low < high) {
            int pivotIndex = partition(arr, low, high);
            quickSort(arr, low, pivotIndex);
            quickSort(arr, pivotIndex + 1, high);
        }
    }

    /**
     * Partitions the subarray arr[low...high] using the Hoare scheme
     * 
     * @param arr The array of integers to be partitioned
     * @param low The starting index of the subarray to be partitioned
     * @param high The ending index of the subarray to be partitioned
     * @return The index of the pivot element after partitioning
     */
    public int partition(int[] arr, int low, int high) {
        int pivot = arr[low];
        int i = low - 1;
        int j = high + 1;
        while (true) {
            do {
                i++;
            } while (arr[i] < pivot);

            do {
                j--;
            } while (arr[j] > pivot);

            if (i >= j) {
                return j;
            }

            int temp = arr[i];
            arr[i] = arr[j];
            arr[j] = temp;
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {5, 3, 2, 4, 1};
        QuickSort quickSort = new QuickSort();
        quickSort.quickSort(arr, 0, arr.length - 1);
        System.out.println(Arrays.toString(arr)); // [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
    }
}
```

Note that this implementation sorts the array in place, and the quickSort method recursively sorts subarrays until the entire array is sorted. The partition method is responsible for dividing the array into two partitions around a pivot element, and it returns the index of the pivot element after partitioning. The array is sorted in ascending order.

