In the code snippet you provided, variable `t2` is being assigned the size of the `driver_list::driver(jj).year` plus one. This is used as the second argument to the `strcpy_s` function.

To replace `strcpy_s`, you can modify the code as follows:

```cpp
int t2 = sizeof(driver_list::driver(jj).year) + 1;
if (t2 > t1)
    t2 = t1;
if (t2)
    strncpy(s, driver_list::driver(jj).year, t2 - 1);

s[t2 - 1] = '\0';
```

Here, `strncpy` is used to copy the string `driver_list::driver(jj).year` to `s`, limiting the number of characters copied to `t2 - 1` to avoid buffer overflows (similar to the previous example code). Then, a null character ('\0') is manually added to terminate the string.

